The paper deals with image processing tasks, specifically super-resolution, using deep convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel algorithm that uses attention mechanisms and memory connections, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also deals with remote sensing images, which falls under the category of cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper uses a public dataset to evaluate the proposed algorithm, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
